"reviewcomment":"How could we not check out the oldest restaurant in the worlds?  We did and it was good - Would I go again?  Maybe but probably not for the reason(s) you are thinking.<br>Yes the place is touristy, but who cares! I&#39;m a tourist aren&#39;t I?!? I learned a long time ago just because a place attracts tourist doesn&#39;t mean it can&#39;t be good. <br><br>My wife and I had: a full pitcher of Sangria (Excellent), Shared the Artichokes with Jamon (Drools),  Suckling Pig (pretty good), Suckling Lamb (actually better than the pork in my opinion), and we shared a flan (welcome the surprising star of the show!). and I had an espresso.  <br><br>People say it&#39;s rather pricey - the food listed above came out to 81 Euro and I felt that it was worth it as a whole for the experience.  The staff was excellent and very accommodating.<br><br>Food Ranking Based on what we had here for me:<br>1. Flan (best we had in Spain!)<br>2. Artichokes with Jamon<br>3. Sangria<br>4. Suckling Lamb<br>5. Suckling Pig",
