"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Y2ry0rqc3Y2UI4KOt_LLoQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"When I planned my trip to Madrid, I had a mission to eat as much jamon Iberico as I could. So before I left for Spain, I had bookmarked Museo del Jamon and was determined to stop by before I left the city. Luckily, when my husband and I were walking to the Mercado de San Miguel, we saw the Museo on Calle Mayor. The place did not disappoint and was packed with tourists and locals. The best thing to do is to stand at the bar and order food from the servers. The bar can get packed at times so you&#39;ll have to squeeze between patrons to place an order. It&#39;s a great bargain for food because everything in Europe is expensive. For two bocadillos de jamon and two canas, we spent less than 8 euro total. They even give you a small plate of chorizo sausages for free.<br><br>A great bargain if you love Spanish ham sandwiches but I wouldn&#39;t say it was the best bocadillo I had in Madrid.",
