"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Every time my family and I visit Madrid, we come here, because the food is amazing and it&#39;s pretty cheap.<br><br>It is never empty, the decor is minimalist, and although service is prompt, don&#39;t expect smiles or conversation from the staff...which is just as fine with me, so long as service doesn&#39;t suck.<br><br>There is the regular menu, and the menu del dia for 10 euros (during the day). I have had both, and I can honestly say, everything so far has been excellent. Good portions and good taste. I&#39;ve had their salads, their meatballs and potatoes, their macaroni, their meat and potatoes...I&#39;ve sampled the salmorejo, and the pasta is good as well. If it is available, get the chocolate ice cream with turron...omg. <br><br>The only con is that a small bread is 1 euro. The water bottles are bigger than in other restaurants but to me, they&#39;re still too small. Regardless, I love this place...If you&#39;re too scandalized by prostitutes, I don&#39;t suggest you come here, as they are all over this particular neighborhood...If you&#39;re normal, then I definitely recommend this restaurant!",
