"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/D6ql8tRWB1umQL00AsJFqw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This is such a cool place. Vintage to the max. Thank goodness it&#39;s right around the corner from my boyfriend&#39;s place. Between HD Cafteria and its across-the-street neighbor Tierra, we&#39;ve always got good options to choose from. The decor and &#34;feel&#34; of the place leave nothing to be desired. It reminds me of an old American diner, actually, but not in the tacky 1950&#39;s way, more the retro, classy, comfortable way of a cafeteria. <br><br>For some reason, my first time I was there, everyone kept dropping everything. It was quite funny as waiters dropped a couple of items, I dropped my napkin, other guests seemed to drop cutlery, etc. Totally just a chance thing, but it was a fun way to remember the restaurant. Very memorable first experience.<br><br>It&#39;s just gotten better and better since that time. I like how they deep fry the cheddar cheese for the burgers, making it into a crispy sheet of deliciousness. Most recently we tried one of the salads, and though it was a bit on the smaller side, it was definitely tasty. I haven&#39;t tried the desserts yet, so I&#39;ll save that commentary for the next time. As far as drinks, I would recommend the tinto de verano HD with a special anis liquor. Very, very delicious (you&#39;ll want more than one!). <br><br>The staff is super friendly and hipster in a good way. They just sort of fit. Now that it&#39;s summer, the terraza is in full swing and I&#39;d recommend that you make it your new hot spot on any given summer night.",
