"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"While I&#39;m no expert on Chinese food I can easily say that Ni Hao is my favorite Chinese restaurant in Madrid if not the best I&#39;ve been to in terms of authenticity.<br>My wife and I first went there more or less randomly and then decided to go back TWICE within a week because the waitress was awesome, the food was very good (again, no expert on Chinese food, just my taste buds) and ridiculously cheap compared to any of the chain restaurants on  Gran Via.<br>We speak only a little bit of Spanish and the waitress only spoke a little English, but they have an English menu and you will be able if order anything easily, they will just jump in with whatever soundbites they know in a dozen different languages until it somehow works out.<br>We made an effort to not order anything twice, so we&#39;ve tried over a dozen different things and they were awesome. I agree with previous comments that the Spicy Chicken Sechuan Style is great, but I also enjoyed the Spicy Chicken Ma La very much. You should definitely try their dumpling soup or the &#34;sizzling dumplings&#34;, which are made fresh by the whole family and taste awesome. 5 stars straight!",
