"reviewcomment":"I have been here three times in under a week and I think I have found it to be my go to place for pan con tomate y cafe con leche. <br><br>The cafe con leche is simple, but the pan con tomate is the best I have had so far. The liberally drizzle garlic-infused olive-oil all over this bad boy and it gives it such a wonderful, rich, and unique flavor. And this plate of deliciousness is only 2.20euro.<br><br>And that olive oil, they also used it on my chorizo tosta(only 3euro) and my friends tosta con jamon(4euro). The portions weren&#39;t massive but oh were they satisfying. Again, some of the best of these kinds I&#39;ve food I&#39;ve had in Madrid.<br><br>And I expect to return for dinner one day. Their menu del dia looks fantastic and due to the very positive experiences with the food and the service thus far, I&#39;m expecting another great time.",
