"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Affordable, greasy, and delicious Chinese food hidden below a parking garage. Worth the visit. <br><br>This place is very small, with around 6-8 small tables. For dinner, it helps to come during the less busy hours, which in Spain means anytime between 4 pm and 8 pm. Around 8:30, a line begins to form for those dining in. <br><br>We ordered the fried dumplings, the chow mein, stir fried snap peas, and a pork noodle soup. The noodle soup was hearty and featured thick and chewy handmade noodles in a rich broth with plenty of meat and vegetables. The dumplings were handmade and fried, with thicker wrappers and hearty pieces of pork inside. The chow mein was satisfying- just oily and salty enough. The snap peas were stir fried with garlic and were very fresh. <br><br>The staff are busy but very patient and accommodating. The price was very reasonable, and for people who are craving Chinese food and don&#39;t mind the greasy variety it&#39;s just right!",
