"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I can&#39;t believe I almost missed this place! I researched their hours before arrival and when I got there, I found them closed. After being disappointed, I turned around and found that they have another location right across the street! Make sure you look around before you turn away. <br><br>The restaurant is really small and it&#39;s standing room only, mainly because it&#39;s a quick eatery type of place. The menu is small and they&#39;re known for their gambas al ajillo, garlic shrimp, which is the only thing we ordered before we went to our next dinner. The gambas al ajillo is made on a small stovetop in the restaurant. It&#39;s a very small portion and it&#39;s sizzling in the garlic oil when it&#39;s presented to you. The shrimps are cooked perfectly, there&#39;s chunks of garlic, and you get bread with this. I&#39;ve had this dish at many places and have to say this is the best I&#39;ve ever had. It was sooo good. My only regret is that we didn&#39;t order more!<br><br>Must visit!",
