"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I first heard about Public when a friend told me that she and some friends had stumbled upon a very decently-priced, fairly gourmet restaurant in the center - little did I know that this restaurant is just around the corner from my piso! So, claro, I took her recommendation and decided to try it out for date night.<br><br>We were seated very easily (albeit pretty damn close to the folks next to us, though there were plenty of open tables). Perhaps most eye-catching about this locale are the stellar prices. The decor is elegant and cozy, but gratefully the price point doesn&#39;t escalate to match it.<br><br>We split the guacamole and goat cheese salad and the solomillo. Both were perfectly adequate and not lacking in size. For dessert, we went for the brownie and vanilla ice cream... delicious! Though, be warned, the brownie is extremely rich... probably could have dealt with another scoop of ice cream to balance it out. <br><br>I would say that in a major metropolitan city like Madrid, Public is what we&#39;d call a safe bet. Price is on point, quality is on point, and decoration is too.",
