"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/h1cTprYOr_nrSBLYoS1qpQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"An experience for your palate and eyes.  Each dish is designed and presented beautifully - often with multiple parts and surprises.  Even some of the plates are designed and created (and signed by the chef) specifically for each course.  <br><br>Prefix dinner only - 7 courses for $95 or 13 for $145.  They start off the meal with a poem of sorts - explaining the chef&#39;s inspiration.  They also explicitly say, no dessert, but we were surprised with one at the end!<br><br>We got the 7 course dinner (again, all pre-fix, so you can&#39;t order):<br><br>Edemame with olive and yuzu sauce<br><br>Young coconut soup with beans, scallops, clams, caviar; Sardine skewers came out midway through this course - You HAVE to scrape the coconut out of the shell, so yummy.  We saw some newbs leave the coconut - what a waste!<br><br>Toasted squid, strawberry, yogurt, coffee (&#34;kimchi&#34;) - interesting sweet flavor.<br><br>Partridge broth with eel, tomato and, eel skin; also partridge toast and baby eel came out midway - The baby eels were a little weird (imagine a pile of thin worms...  eek)<br><br>Tuna cheek (tastes like beef!) with peas, potato, mushrooms; Bone marrow on a potato came out mid - you get it...<br><br>Hayck? (some sort fish) chin with foie gras, mushrooms<br><br>White asparagus with venison, citrus zest; Toast with pâté of red mallard<br><br>Shrimp marinated in bone of red mallard; Red mallard with shrimp head and caviar<br><br>Brioche with oxtail and quail egg - This dish was GORGEOUS - a little bun with an egg perfectly on top<br><br>Cakes with grapefruit gels, foam, ice cream with a surprise mustard garnish (could have done without the mustard - they actually told us not to touch a small sphere on the side, then the waiter swooped in midway and smashed the mustard on our plates!)<br><br>If you count all the different parts of courses, we technically got In 10 dishes total.  Was it the best meal I&#39;ve ever had?  Hard to say, but definitely an experience.",
