"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Looking in from the street, chances are you won&#39;t be lured in. That&#39;s because the real crowd (at least when I came) can be found on the beautiful patio out back. We saddled up on one of the high-top stools and were waited on immediately. The first that that caught my eye was the long list of interesting drinks from tinto de verano made with white wine to cider sangria. Everything we tried was refreshing and came in their own can, making it more special. <br><br>I didn&#39;t find the food too bad either. I was impressed by their wide array of salad choices, something not too common here in Spain. Once I saw that 2 of their 3 &#34;menu del dia&#34; options included your choice of salad, I knew I would go with that. Their tapas are unique- with many things coming encased in a mini bread bowl. To top it off, the food is served in a chic brown box and our waitress knew just how to arrange all four of our meals to fit just right. <br><br>Sure the salad was doused in too much dressing but I can get over that. Outside on their nice patio on an afternoon day, this would still be one of my favorite spots in the area.",
