"reviewcomment":"Thanks to previous reviewer as I came to have the Frances brunch.  It came with a basket of delicious regular sized pastries, two toasts with smoked salmon with poached eggs and jam and hollandaise sauce on the side.  As well, it had tea and orange juice.  Hefty for 14 euros and it could feed 2-3 people.  The eggs were pretty well done but I did not care as it was as close to brunch as I could get and yes it does feed two people.  So much so that the gentleman I shared the table with took the time to google translate to me that he cannot believe how much I eat.  I only shrugged and smiled, harder to explain I am taking most of it to go.  Lots of tourists were there since it is what you would expect from the usual cafe in North America except that the tea serving is still so pitifully small.  I enjoyed sitting in my sunny spot and got a chance to write in my journal.  I felt like I was closer to home in this place.  The service is friendly albeit they spoke very little English but I appreciate them trying to serve me as best they can even neatly packing my food to go.<br><br>If you need a touch of home come here and enjoy the delicious food.",
