"reviewcomment":"I really like this place! I&#39;ve been here a number of times and yes, its a dirty hole-in-the-wall, but if you&#39;re down for that sort of thing, they give VERY generous tapas when you order a drink.  They don&#39;t serve normal-sized cañas, only jarras (the personal size, it&#39;s like a beer mug), and it&#39;s about 2.50€, but they give you a plate of paella, stew, or tortilla española with it.  Of course the tapas are hit-and-miss; on a good day you get paella, on a bad day you get bad sausage.  For the most part you get something good, and if you finish the first tapa they give you another one!  It&#39;s a cheap place to drink and fill up, and I actually really like their paella. (You can also order a ración of paella for 10€, good enough for a few people, if you don&#39;t get it as a tapa).  If you&#39;re looking for tapas, this is one of the few places in Madrid where you&#39;ll get more than a few olives or patatas bravas with your drink.",
