"reviewcomment":"This is a very good tapas bar, but as ricard67 points out, it&#39;s best for its excellent wine selection. The tapas themselves are excellent (although I wasn&#39;t nuts about the jamon and manchego plate they served), but there are only 4 or 5 tables which seem to get filled up by about 10, just an hour or so after the place opens. They also take reservations here, so if you want to be sure you have a table, either reserve one or arrive at 8:30.<br><br> My experience with the service was that it was also that it was (mostly) super-friendly -- and knowledgeable. When I visited with my girlfriend, we tried about 5 different wines (we also had a bottle of the delicious Camins del Priorat) and all were amazing. One of them, the 2003 Alion (Ribera del Duero) was truly astounding. The cost to open it was only 36 or 37EUR, though here in Freiburg, Germany I saw it for 45 or 50EUR in a store.<br><br> Next time I go to Madrid I will definitely be coming here again. On the night I visited, my girlfriend and I went to about 5 other bars on Cava Baja, and this really was the best one. 4 stars as a tapas place, 5 as a wine bar.",
