"reviewcomment":"We stumbled upon this pizzeria one night after attending a show in the nearby Teatro Lara, and I&#39;m glad we did. First impression: lots of maja folks in attendance. Granted, it was a Friday night, but we did end up having to sit at the bar due to lack of available seats. We were very well attended by an adorable little Italian guy, and we settled on some vino, beer, the chef salad, and some pizza. The pesto pizza was especially commendable. We also enjoyed the olives given with our drinks. They were true to the restaurant&#39;s name - MUCHO ajo (garlic)! I&#39;d recommend that have some mints or chewing gum after consuming them and before meeting your significant other. <br><br>The decorations were cool as well. Had some bike paraphernalia and low lighting. Bathroom was spacious and the noise level wasn&#39;t too bad. Match all that with free wifi (I&#39;m such a sucker for free wifi), and you&#39;ve got yourself quite a nice place for a casual/cozy dinner experience. All that&#39;s missing is you!",
