"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"The decor drew us in - local art, plush chairs with checkerboard tables, and a nude mannequin torso on the bar wearing a fedora. But what makes the place really special is what the bar is all about. When the rest of the city is closed and quiet, the basement brick cave of El Camerino (the name of the bar part of this business) is bumping with live funk for a local crowd of actors and musicians drinking cocktails beer and wine and enjoying the afternoon doing something besides sleeping. Next door is a pizza place which can actually be accessed through an underground passage behind the performance room, which is also used for theatre, cabarets, monologues, and short film screenings. At night DJ&#39;s take over and spin funk, and the owner refuses to give exact closing times because it all depends on the vibe on a given day. Its a celebration of local culture, and the food is pretty rocking too. Live jam session (guests welcome) every Saturday starting at 3pm. Just the kind of cool this city needs more injections of.",
