"categorystrlist":"Steakhouses,         Basque,         Spanish",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/COLkSPFzYJfCnfN3Nlhiyg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"We had dinner here on our last night in Madrid before we headed back to New York. This restaurant was recommended to us by our concierge and it turned out to be a pretty good meal. Even though it was another expensive restaurant (which I do not mind as long as the food is good), the rib steak for two was soft, tender and delicious. They give you delicious bread with great olive oil, complimentary olives and small chorizos as a starter and we ordered the grilled asparagus which were excellent. The steak is delivered to your table sliced and raw along with a scalding &#34;asador&#34; which is a very hot grilling plate. You place the meat on it and cook it yourself and this was very simple and quick. We got some cut up strawberries and a lemon sorbet drink (complimentary) and ordered the rice pudding which was very good.<br><br>The service was excellent but the reason I gave 4 stars is because the man who took our order not only forgot to bring us one of the appetizers but he also never submitted the rice pudding order either. I would recommend this restaurant if you are in the mood for steak. The high cost of the meal is about the same price as we pay for any good steak restaurant on the North Shore of Long Island except that they do not even have a line on the charge slip to add a tip. The meal came to $162 including 2 glasses of very good sangria and one cappuccino.<br><br> Visited May 2013",
