"reviewcomment":"This is by far my favorite neighborhood cafe/bar. It has a very rustic and home like feel, as evidenced with the mismatched furniture. No table service here, take a look at the menu and order at the counter. They have a range of coffee drinks, teas, traditional Spanish chocolate and other tasty treats. I usually find myself here with good friends discussing the events of the day or week. The ambiance is quiet, relaxed, great. They even allow dogs inside! The bathrooms are small and quaint but that&#39;s fairly normal around Spain. My only wish is that they had more space, as sometimes getting a table can be a challenge. Definitely my favvvvvvorite neighborhood establishment by leaps and bounds.<br><br>P.S. No credit cards accepted! Standard Spanish tradition.",
