"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ApEyEVIa0D_VNLipWwEPVQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Although the design of this restaurant tries to give the impression of a high-class, high-quality Asian restaurant, most of the dishes I tried here were mediocre at best. My friend and I decided to try one of the tasting menus (the menu Teppanyaki), and while it wasn&#39;t completely awful, it did not seem worth the price of 31 euros.<br><br>The sushi/sashimi plate did not taste particularly fresh to me, and the teppanyaki was juicy but bland. The &#34;Cantonese rice&#34; lacked flavor as well, and the dessert (a standard tiramisu) tasted more like a frozen cheesecake. The only parts of the menu that I was actually quite pleased with were the seaweed salad starter (which is kind of hard to mess up given that it&#39;s a cold dish) and the vegetable tempura (which were fresh and hot).<br><br>While the food did not leave me particularly satisfied or pleased, I will say that the atmosphere here is quite nice. The servers are attentive and extremely polite, and if judged solely by appearance, I would say that this is a very aesthetic and up-scale restaurant.<br><br>At the end of the day however, I just do not think that the prices are appropriate for the quality of food they serve.",
