"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"It&#39;s a shame about El Automático.  It&#39;s a cool, funky little spot in the great, diverse, hip neighborhood of Lavapies, and the food is pretty good- I like the salmorejo con bacalao (andalusian tomato soup with smoked cod!) and the cañas (little beer) are cold and fresh.  But the waitstaff-bartenders are the pits.  Seriously, they need attitude adjustments in a big way.  And it&#39;s always the same people behind the bar!  I&#39;ve always assumed that when the staff are rude and dismissive they are unhappy with the management, are having a bad day or something like that, but these are the same miserable lot every time we&#39;ve popped in for a visit.  They just won&#39;t quit.  They revel in what appears to be self-imposed misery.  And, yes, we are stubborn, we keep giving it a chance because their menu is different from the traditional Spanish bar, we like the decor, the beers, the people watching and my husband and I went there on our first date.  But the staff!  Please, if you choose to brave this popular haunt, best just ignore the jerk that pours your beer with a sneer and not take it AT ALL personally.",
