"reviewcomment":"This is a real Mexican Mexican food restaurant (not tex mex).. Coming this comment from a Mexican girl.<br>Almost every plate comes as a &#34;taco&#34;, made with fresh hand made tortillas. Everything is gluten free (except desserts), so it&#39;s a really good option for someone who is not tolerant to gluten. The prices are high, but I think they&#39;re worth it, although the service is a little bit slow, the food is delicious.<br>You have vegetarian dishes, meat options and seafood.<br>Also, the cocktails are excellent, we tried one called mezcaliña, made with ginger, lime and mezcal, delicious!<br>It is not the typical Mexican restaurant where everyone is with a Mexican sombrero &amp; mustache, and the music is loud; no, this is a gourmet restaurant where there is a quiet, nice, environment.<br>It&#39;s difficult to get a table, so you need to make a 2 week in advance reservation to be sure. There are not to many tables, it&#39;s a small, intimate place.<br>PD: you should like spicy food to go to this restaurant!",
