"reviewcomment":"This AYCE restaurant is located in the Plaza Mayor area.  I have to say that I was extremely impressed with this restaurant, not because the food is worldclass caliber. I loved it because it is good value for the money at EU 9.95 per person.  Seriously, in Madrid EU 9.95 would only buy you a snack i.e. a cappuccino, a muffin and a bottled water.  The buffet is quite extensive with so many offerings like different types of salads, pastas, soup, hot dishes (fried chicken wings, roasted chicken, pizza, pork stew, braised ham hock, paella, desserts, etc.  The drinks are also included with the price.  You can also opt for beer instead of softdrinks...now that to me, is super awesome.<br><br>I thought everything on the buffet were very good and I have to give 4-5 stars for the hot dishes.  The service is very friendly, the counter girl even asked me how to say fork, spoons and knives...as a grouping (asking me while she does her hand gestures...so cute) in English....I said...&#34;silverware&#34;.  The place is small but there is a second floor dining area too.  The restrooms are clean and  have papertowels vs hand dryer...that&#39;s a plus for me.  <br><br>I highly recommend this AYCE restaurant to people who are planning on visiting Madrid.  Bookmark this place, try it out (specially when you are running low on money), then you can thank me later.<br><br>PS.  I was going to take a photo of the buffet but opted not to since a lot of businesses in Europe do not allow people to take photos inside their establishments...I respect that.",
