"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"This establishment has been around for years.  Probably around 20 or more.  I&#39;ve been frequenting this restaurant-bar since my husband introduced me to the place 9 years ago.  Not much has changed since then.  It&#39;s a great place to meet up for beer, cider and eats.  The beer on tap is good and fresh.  The food, as well.  I&#39;ve had most of the tapas on the menu, save for many of the meat dishes since I&#39;m a vegetarian (I eat seafood, though), and they are always fresh, delicious, and the portions hugely satisfying.  The place will get pretty packed on evening (meaning 10pm onward) weekends, but there is ample room.  The bar has many stools and a side bar where you can also stand, socialize and chow down.  There are also many tables, big and small.  The service is solid.  The waitstaff are efficient and have a nice, wry Spanish sense of humor.  Stand out tapas:  Pastel de cabracho (fish pudding), chopitos (fried baby squid), and patatas con cabrales (potatoes with strong blue cheese sauce).  The bread is heavenly. And best of all, it&#39;s easy on the pocket book.  A stellar find.",
