"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Definitely, a very good place to go if you like meat. The Almuerzo de la vaca menu is amazing value for money, but it&#39;s only available Monday to Friday at lunch time. For 15EUR you can have a small starter (hummus with bread), big beef steak with a quite big side (choosing from roasted vegetables, salad, chips and peppers), 1/2 bottle wine, beer or soft drink and a homemade dessert plus coffee.<br>I went here with some work colleagues. I&#39;m not a fan of red meat, and apart from the steak, you can choose salmon or sardines as main, but given the name of the restaurant (The cow Veronica), I decided I should give it a try. It was very good indeed, although I could only eat half (even though I didn&#39;t try the starter and my side of choice was salad). For dessert, everyone in my table recommended the homemade ice cream so I tried fig and raspberry. I didn&#39;t really like it, but I&#39;m quite demanding with ice cream. Raspberry is not a sorbet and none of the two flavours was very creamy.<br>Service was fast and very friendly, and although I wouldn&#39;t come here again, I totally recommend it and understand that for meat lovers this place is a must.",
