"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Looking to appease an intense craving for Indian, me and my friend knew Lavapies would deliver. We were recommended this place and told it was some of the cheapest around but still the best. We were immediately seated upon walking in but by the time we left a little after 10, the place was packed. The friendly servers were very attentive and let us take our time looking at the menu but were fast to grab our order when we were ready. <br><br>When we sat, we were given the Indian equivalent of chips and salsa. The green sauce was fresh and tangy and made for a nice starter. For food, we went with chicken tikka, saag paneer, garlic naan and some plain white rice (which you have to order separately). All of it was delicious- especially the chicken and naan. The bill didn&#39;t even surpass 20 Euro and we left very full and happy!<br><br>In a neighborhood packed with Indian restos, I think I will rely on this one for when I&#39;m in the mood.",
