"rating":"2.5",
"reviewcomment":"I approached Bangkok with low expectations, despite the reommendation of a friend. My experiences with ethnic food in Madrid have been dismal at best. The Thai food here though was dare I say it decent. Maybe even a bit better than decent, tasty.<br><br>We arrived just before the normal Spanish lunch hour (2-2:30) securing the best seat in the restaurant next to the window overlooking Arenal. Great for puppy watching. <br><br>Despite it being a Saturday the menu del dia (2 courses, a dessert and drink) was in full effect. I ordered the tallerines, pad thai for my first pate, green curry chicken for my second and a tea for dessert. They had about five options for each plate. Everything came out fast and piping hot. The green curry chicken was a bit too spicy for my bf, but typical spice level for green curry. By our second plate the restaurant really started to fill in. <br><br>The service was typical in Spain. No smiling waiters, no niceties. But I appreciated the efficiency. At 12€ each I left pretty satisfied.",
