"categorystrlist":"Spanish",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/8MBWEr4bczrTnY3L7rnuAg/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"This was good for me, bad for my wife.  Just in from barcelona, we were staying our last night in spain near the Atocha train station.  The previous week, we were near La Latina, and had tried lots of tapas places.  Wanting to stay nearby, our hotel receptionist recommended this place since it was just down the street.  She told us that it was traditional Spanish food.  Well, I liked my meal.  We started with octopus cooked in butter and salt.  Again, I liked it, my wife decided that she does not like octopus, in comparison to calamari.  I had the roasted, suckling pig that came with fries and grilled peppers.  I thought it was excellent, and had been want to try this through our vacation.  It is basically the same as Filipino lechon, which I love.  Anyhow, my wife got a fillet of sole grilled.  She found it very plain, and regretted not ordering the version with meuniere sauce.  So... I&#39;d recommend this place if you want traditional Spanish food.  My wife was disappointed, but I think she ordered the wrong things for her taste.",
