"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I give this 5-star review with the minor disclaimer that we did not try too many items.  That said, the steak tartare and grilled duck breast were fantastic, and the fried hake pretty good.  The tartare was a generous portion and the duck, while smaller, had excellent flavor and a nice crispiness to the fat/skin and was complimented perfectly by spiced pears soaked in wine.  The wines seemed reasonably priced, and even the 13 euro/bottle &#34;Roble&#34; level RDD wine was very drinkable, and available by the glass, though not indicated on the menu.<br><br>Our waiter, the manager, and other waiters passing by all did there utmost to ensure that we had everything we needed and were satisfied with the meal.  The check came with an &#34;invitation&#34; to try a free shot of an herbal liqueur.  <br><br>One warning:  though it was posted in a couple different places, I did not realize until it was too late that there was a 15% surcharge for eating at the tables on the sidewalk. <br><br>Though you can certainly find quality food for less in other parts of Madrid, I was very pleasantly surprised to find Chulapa in this touristy area.",
