"rating":"2.5",
"reviewcomment":"With rumbling stomachs calling out for some paella, we headed to Costa Blanca Arroceria conveniently located close by. We couldn&#39;t wait too late to eat so were some of their first customers for the evening and the waitstaff was perfectly accommodating. <br><br>They started by bringing us 3 huge pieces of bread which we necessarily weren&#39;t in the mood for and almost regretted touching when we saw it cost us 6 Euros. However, we looked past that and were glad to get plenty of olives with our pitcher of sangria and an order of calamari on the house. Our waitress was even kind enough to bring a whole pitcher of water which was appreciated later on in the meal. <br><br>We went with the paella mixta and it came out piping hot and delicious. The seafood was plentiful and the pieces of chicken also great. It was so hard to stop eating but the three of us were so full after only digging into about half of it. <br><br>The whole meal came out to about 17 per person which isn&#39;t bad considering how full and satisfied we were. I&#39;d definitely come back and recommend it to anyone looking for quality rice.",
