"rating":"2.5",
"reviewcomment":"Just when I had all but given up on my search for decently priced yet quality sushi in Madrid, a friend stepped in with this recommendation. I will admit I was a bit (ok very) skeptical when I heard that not only was it good sushi, but also an all-you-can-eat joint for only 11.50. However, she was insistent so I decided to try it out when I was in dire need of a sushi fix. <br><br>The place was packed on a Sunday afternoon so I took that as a good sign. On top of that, the staff was not very friendly so I could only assume the food must be good if so many people were there when nothing else was striking. They gave us our paper menu to order and we started penciling in all that we wanted. The food came out at lightning speed which was nice because we were starving. Word to the wise- do not order everything at once. If so, you will end up with a full table with more than you will want to eat. Instead, take it in multiple rounds and your stomach will thank you later. <br><br>I made it a point to be close to starving before this outing so I could eat a lot and eat a lot I did! Go for the dumplings, California rolls, temaki and maki. Skip the edamame (mushy), tempura (too much oily batter) and noodles (too slimy). Also, know that the drinks are not included but overall, you get way more than you would pay for at your standard sushi spot.",
