"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/V9n-qdcVESPg-HdeDM3fsA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"With a wonderful location across from the Park Retiro, Azabal is a perfect way to conclude a long stroll around the park.  They have large wine list with selections all along the price spectrum.  Since i t was the last night in Madrid for one our our party, we decided to celebrate properly with an expensive bottle.  The staff was polite enough to notify us that it was the last bottle, so we&#39;d need to switch to another wine once we&#39;d finished that first bottle.  That was not a problem for us since we planned on buying the cheapest bottle after splurging, since the first bottle was so good that anything after would surely taste like two buck chuck in comparison.<br>The service here was excellent, they filled our wine glasses, water glasses, and swapped out the plates and silverware between courses.  The food was superb, all the dishes were subtly flavorful and simply presented.  They don&#39;t have an English menu, but the waitress translated every item on the menu for us.<br>Afterward we went in search for a Gin and tonic bar, only to learn that Azabal has a reputation for making a top notch gin tonic.  May try to get back and try it.",
