"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Need to preface this with the following: I&#39;m half Argentine -- the half that loves cows that are lovingly grass fed in the Pampas and get to soak up the sun. La Cabaña is the second best Argentine steakhouse I&#39;ve been to in my LIFE. <br><br>If you&#39;re curious, my number one favorite is in Buenos Aires (La Brigada, get the entraña al punto). But I digress. La Cabaña&#39;s entraña al punto is the kind of meal I&#39;ll remember fondly years from now--just as I&#39;ve salivated over memories of my dinner at La Brigada. <br><br>Located walking distance from Plaza de Santa Ana, we got there at 9PM, which we thought was late enough. Dinner doesn&#39;t usually start until 11PM in Madrid, so bring the TUMS. By 10PM the restaurant was completely full (on a weekday), so reservations are recommended.<br><br>It&#39;s so rare to get a steak so perfectly executed that it requires no salt, sauce, bread or fixings. Argentine steak is typically served at a perfect pink medium (al punto) with a crispy crust and mega moist middle. Our steaks were served on a communal platter that arrived sizzling and could have easily served 3-4. I said could have. We had no problems devouring it--every bite coupled with a head shake and close of the eyes to soak in the experience.",
