"categorystrlist":"Basque",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/BRcP31yXYIa9oKaskXJCzg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Headline: Good food seems to find you in Madrid<br><br>Yep - still in Madrid.  Dantxari was picked by the Frenchman in our party.  You can&#39;t really go wrong when the French approve.  One thing I totally approve of with this restaurant, aside from it&#39;s rustic interior and no fuss service, was the small pieces of chorizo that were served prior to the meal.  They made a great accompaniment to the bread basket (which was also delicious).<br><br>For our appetizer course, we ordered the cod croquettes, which were larger than others I have seen.  They were crispy on the outside, light and fluffy on the inside and totally delicious.  They are a must-order.  In addition, we ordered the Piquillo Peppers stuffed with crab.  Although they were good, they weren&#39;t in the same league as the cod croquettes.<br><br>For my main course, I went with the waiters suggestion and ordered the Monkfish with garlic.  You can&#39;t really go wrong in Spain with seafood, and this was no exception.  The garlic was a little weak, but the monkfish is such a delicate fish that you wouldn&#39;t want it any stronger.  <br><br>The same warnings go with this as with other restaurants in Madrid - you get a better chance of getting a table earlier, and drink the local wines and beers - they are just plain better.",
