"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Ethiopian food holds a special place in my heart. I don&#39;t know how my love affair began but it started when I was really young and has never ended. I decided it was time to see what Madrid had to offer in terms of Ethiopian restos so decided to give Nuria a shot. <br><br>I was anxious to say the least but calmed down with one sip of the sweet honey wine which I had never tried before. I liked the authenticity of drinking it out of the carafe and got excited to see what else was in store. We went with a couple meat platters and the vegetarian combo that gives you a bit of everything. The place wasn&#39;t too crowded so it didn&#39;t take us too long to get our food. Once it came, I don&#39;t think me and my date spoke to each other until all of our injera (the bread you eat with) was gone and we needed more to finish all the food. <br><br>The waiters were friendly and even encouraged us to eat all the injera soaked in the juices from the food which was a plus in my book. Although they were miffed when we didn&#39;t order dessert and tried to annoyingly guilt us into ordering more, I was so content and stuffed to the brim with the main course that I couldn&#39;t even care. I didn&#39;t come with too high of expectations with fear of being disappointed but this definitely fit the bill.",
