"reviewcomment":"A fresh, floral and fun bar amidst the hot, Spanish streets of Madrid. I love this bar, and wish I could take it back with me to Edinburgh. I came here after a long night out, so was tired and a little &#34;delicate&#34;; so didn&#39;t partake of many drinks or food. But just sitting with a chilled group of people, enjoying vermouth or gin and tonics (out of giant wine glasses, which I have decided is my new favourite way to drink gin), with friendly staff, other chilled customers, a puppy party in the corner, wide open windows that let in some fresh air, and the very fresh decor -- tiles, flowers on the tables, and tying in to the &#34;Verbana&#34; rose garden theme without being ott. It&#39;s just my perfect idea of a Sunday afternoon g&amp;t with friends bar.<br><br>In fact, I won&#39;t take it back to Edinburgh with me. I&#39;ll move to Madrid instead and make it my local. Gracias.",
