"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/54m2aDt_O2UOCHSRk10YcA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Our hotel recommended this place, and I&#39;m so glad we listened to him instead of experimenting on our own. This place has DELICIOUS tapas! We couldn&#39;t decide, so we got the tapas menu. It wasn&#39;t cheap (roughly 80 Euros for 2, without drinks), but it was SO GOOD! Definitely worth it. It was like a 9 course meal. Except usually in multi-course meals, there are always a few courses that aren&#39;t so good, but at La Bocaito, everything was amazing. I couldn&#39;t decide which tapa was my favorite! This has to be in the top 5 meals I&#39;ve ever had, and I&#39;m a foodie.<br><br>Plus, it&#39;s super cute inside, like a Granada cave, and the service is excellent. we never had to wait more than a few minutes for the next course, and even though none of our servers spoke English (just the lady who seated us), they went out of their way to explain what each tapa was. <br><br>The only problem was that it turns out they charge a couple euros for the bread that&#39;s on each table when you come in. We didn&#39;t touch ours but we still had to pay, so just beware - if you don&#39;t want to pay for bread in Spain, tell them to take it away right when you get there.",
