"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/eb0PPqFLgkXOrGYyj4PZQQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"After traveling for over 2 weeks now, I started to crave eating Asian food and our next city was Madrid so the first thing I did was research where can I eat at?? I found this place close to where we were staying at and ran here once we drop off our bag. I didn&#39;t eat all day until around 10ish at night because I had the biggest hang over ever. We open the door and this place was pack but lucky we found a table to sit at right away. I look over the menu and wanted to order 6-7 items for 2 people and my gf look at me if I was crazy so I trim down to 4 items which was still alot but I didn&#39;t care. First came the kim chi and it was very salted but tasty so I ate like first. Next came the bimbebio and that was actually pretty tasty. The rice was crispy and burnt and gooey in the middle. The beef rib came after that and we cook it up ourselves. It was half fatty but tasty pretty good. Later on came the spicy noodle soup and the broth was very good but the noodle tasty and look exactly like pasta lol...It was gross!<br>Plus they have red and green bellpepper in it and that obvisely the Spanish influence in it. I just drink the soup and threw away everything in it. My gf has a beer w/this dinner and I just had water. The meal was good but i think the quality is just ok. I was extremely hungry for not eating all day so that made the food taste better then it suppose to. The price of this meal wasn&#39;t really cheap, it cost around 42 euro for korean. Would i come back here, yes but for only certain things.",
