"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Let me just preface this by saying that I grew up in Nebraska, so part of my rating may be rooted in nostalgia...<br><br>I was studying abroad in Spain when I first spotted Cafeteria Nebraska, and I knew I wanted to return when my dad came to visit me. <br><br>We were delighted to be there...Nebraska doesn&#39;t get much glory in the states. We sat down at a table next to a big wall mural of what looked like a northern woods landscape. We told our waiter that we were from Nebraska, and he asked us if it looked like the picture. We chuckled and said it more closely resembled somewhere like Wisconsin or North Dakota,  but I&#39;m pretty sure he wasn&#39;t familiar with those states. Not that I expected him to.<br><br>It was my dad&#39;s first night in Madrid, so I suggested he get something iconic. Or iconic with Americans. Churros y chocolate! They were tasty, I had a few nibbles. The chocolate was perfect, a nice thick consistency almost like pudding. Great for dipping!<br><br>I ordered a sanwich mixto (ham and cheese toasted) and a draft beer. The sandwich was hot and satisfied my craving for manchego cheese. <br><br>Overall, I&#39;m glad to finally have written this review, even if it was a few years late. I can still remember it very clearly, which is a great testament to the restaurant and its owners :)<br><br>[Quiero escribir esta critica en espanol, pero mi teclado no funcionara...]",
