"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/jgQhmeeTETBv92ofa6Fz8A/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Stumbled by this gem while wandering through Madrid. Very near the Royal Palace. While I was there I don&#39;t think there was one tourist so I enjoyed being immersed in the Spanish culture. I was greeted by David the head waiter. He made the experience complete. Very knowledgable about absolutely everything in the restaurant. Sat in the beautiful down stairs dinning room that used to be used as a secret tunnel for the Royal Palace. Ordered a steak and my girlfriend ordered the pork &#39;presa&#39;. The &#39;presa&#39; was the best pork cut that I have ever had. Highly recommend. The cuts of meat were amazing and perfectly cooked. They offered a 1 kilo t-bone that I would have definitely ordered if I had been more hungry. They have an excellent selection of wine to pair with your meal. They also offer the iconic Jamon Iberico which is on display throughout the bar area. Prices were very reasonable for the quality of the food compared to some the other restaurants I ate in the previous couple of days of my trip in Madrid. Can not wait to go back and visit this outstanding restaurant in the center of Madrid. Make sure you ask for David and you will not be disappointed. A++",
