"reviewcomment":"I had a wonderful evening at La Farfalia!<br><br>It was one of those late night, meet up with friends after the show: &#34;where shall we go to eat?&#34; <br>&#34;I don&#39;t care! I&#39;m so hungry let&#39;s just go somewhere close!&#34; <br>&#34;I know a place! Follow me.&#34;<br>&#34;Hey it&#39;s closed!&#34;<br>&#34;But Yelp says it&#39;s open!&#34;<br>&#34;That&#39;s the way it is in August in Madrid.&#34;<br>&#34;Ok. I know another place.&#34;<br>&#34;Can&#39;t we just go to that Chinese place right there?&#34;<br>&#34;No. That place is no good.&#34;<br>&#34;Follow me!&#34;<br>&#34;This is so far.&#34;<br>&#34;How long are we going to be walking.&#34;<br>&#34;I&#39;m SO hungry.&#34;<br>&#34;What is this place called?&#34;<br>&#34;La Farfalla.&#34;<br>&#34;That&#39;s Italian for Butterfly.&#34;<br>&#34;That&#39;s right.&#34;<br>&#34;The George Clooney character&#39;s girlfriend in The American calls him Senor Farfalla.&#34;<br>&#34;Oh... That&#39;s right...&#34;<br>... kind of summer evenings in Madrid.<br><br>Once we got there it was like one of those happy scenes in a Fellini movie. Food and wine coming from all directions feeding into a big table full of conversations.<br><br>Good sausage. Good pizza. Good steaks. Good salads. Good wine. Good beer.<br><br>Worth the wait. Worth the walk.",
