"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/k6sAD7EMwJiD5kgjuAsvLA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"For dinner last weekend, Mexican was what everyone wanted and so we were determined to find it. I remembered passing by this place en route to other locales many times and always thought it looked promising so decided to give it a try. We were dining on the early side, but the staff was willing to flip on the light switches of their back dining room and allow us to be the first customers for the night! <br><br>I liked the atmosphere from the start. It fit the Mexican theme yet was cozy and comfortable unlike some other restaurants. We were promptly given menus and gave our order. A couple of us got the chicken tamales while another at the table got the chicken burrito. It actually ended up being beef but we were all too hungry to complain and send it back. My order of tamales came alongside delicious guac, fresh pico de gallo and an actual spicy sauce that I layered on top. They were filling but definitely did not put me over the edge. Thankfully, my friend&#39;s burrito was HUGE and so I eagerly helped her finish it. <br><br>The service wasn&#39;t overwhelmingly kind but we left feeling full and happy. It is not on the cheap side but when you just need to satisfy that Mexican craving, it fits the bill.",
