"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/assets/2/www/img/76df14aad260/default_avatars/business_large_square.png",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"After visiting the Temple de Debod I was looking for a quaint non-touristy place to grab a bite to eat. I first wandered around the neighborhood landing at a cute little bar. Because I couldn&#39;t interpret the menu (all in Spanish) and it seemed expensive I chose to wander elsewhere after having a drink. Google maps pulled up La Creperie, and I love crepes, so I headed straight there (even though average reviews were a 3 star).<br><br>Packed quaint, small 2-room restaurant. All (or what appeared to be) locals in groups 4-5 or couples present along with some families. Service was quick and thorough. I was able to ask for a glass of water in Spanish and they actually brought a whole pitcher! (nice! free water in Europe is rare). <br><br>A large menu of crepe options (regular and sweet(dulces)). I enjoyed the Roma and it was quite filling. I liked the vibe and culture and hope to go back before I leave Madrid!",
