"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"When in Madrid, do as the Spaniards would do.  In Spain there are many complaints of slow service, however that is a standard and should not be considered an insult.  Waiters were always polite and if I needed something, would simply smile at one and hold up my index finger.  <br><br>This was my favorite place to have a drink.  Why?  Cava was less than 5e, the view and location were excellent and the tapas were always above average.  One time the tapas were a plate of chocolate covered peanuts and mini gum drops! Once it was a small plate of paella.  <br><br>I ate lunch once, and while it is something I would never order again (I typically don&#39;t eat fried foods and it was fried calamari), it was very good.  The waiters will not rush you even if you want to linger over a drink for hours.  <br><br>I&#39;ll give this warning in all restaurants in madrid.  You will be charged 1e for bread whether you want it or not so expect it.",
